org.apache.ignite.internal.util

Class GridBoundedConcurrentOrderedMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentSkipListMap<K,V>
        • org.apache.ignite.internal.util.GridBoundedConcurrentOrderedMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, ConcurrentMap<K,V>, ConcurrentNavigableMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>, NavigableMap<K,V>, SortedMap<K,V>

    public class GridBoundedConcurrentOrderedMap<K,V>
extends ConcurrentSkipListMap<K,V>
    Concurrent ordered map that automatically manages its maximum size. Once it exceeds its maximum, it will start removing smallest elements until the maximum is reached again. If optional listener is set via evictionListener(org.apache.ignite.lang.IgniteBiInClosure) method, then listener will be notified for every eviction.

    Note that due to concurrent nature of this map, it may grow slightly larger than its maximum allowed size, but in this case it will quickly readjust back to allowed size.

    Note that remove(Object) and remove(Object, Object) methods are not supported for this kind of map.
